dashboard.definition:
{
	"title": "mask_and_clone",
	"description": "",
	"inputs": {},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem description\nSome data contains private or secret information like user names and passwords that it is inappropiate for all eyes to see. Under these circumstances data needs to be hidden from those users, for instance 1st line support. However this we may still need to keep the orginal data for other reasons, for higher security level users. Splunk doesn't allow for selective masking at point of search, which is a significant challenge for any unstructured data system. \n\n## Existing Solutions\nSplunk documentation a section on how to [Anonymize data|https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/8.0.6/Data/Anonymizedata]. However this is destructive to the orignal event and the ability to see the orginal event is lost. \n\n## Proposed Solution\n`CLONE_SOURCETYPE` offers us the abilty to create two copies of the event and treat them differently. It is possible to implement this solution using entirely using the `INGEST_EVAL` and `replace()`, but in the interests of using the simplist tool for the job and likely the most efficent due, we will use SEDCMD to implement the usecase. Rather than obterate the user name, we will preserve a few charactors from the user name so that our support personola is able to idenfity likely user names in respone to support calls, while retarding the ability to do analytics on the user name.\n\n###  Example log line\n\n    23:16:25 20-09-23 my email_address=julian@wikileaks.com and my terrible password=\"onetimepassword\"\n\n### The steps performed to process data\n\n1. Clone the `mask_and_clone` sourcetype to a new tempory name `mask_and_clone-clone` with the transform `mask_and_clone-clone`.\n1. With the original event we let flow into the targeted index.\n1. The newly created clone event `mask_and_clone-clone` can have a SEDCMD applied it, so we use this to rewrite the event\n    1. We use a REGEX on the email to remove the middle parts of the email so `rmorgan@splunk.com` becomes `rm..n@s..om` \n    2. We completely oblitate the password and replace it with `######`\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_original": {
			"type": "splunk.events",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_original"
			},
			"options": {
				"list.drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "The orignal event with the user name and password clearly visible"
		},
		"viz_masked": {
			"type": "splunk.events",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_masked"
			},
			"options": {
				"list.drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "The cloned event with the user name and password selectively masked"
		},
		"viz_conf_props": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### props.conf\n\nFrom `default/props.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n# Original event is left untouched and routed to the 'secure' index. The\n# clone (below) gets masking applied and lands in the 'insecure' index.\n[mask_and_clone]\nTIME_PREFIX = ^\nTIME_FORMAT = %H:%M:%S %y-%m-%d\nSHOULD_LINEMERGE=false\nLINE_BREAKER=([\\n\\r]+)\n# Clone the event onto a temporary sourcetype so the masking pipeline runs\n# only on the copy.\nTRANSFORMS-apply-masking=mask_and_clone-clone\n\n# The cloned event: mask sensitive fields with SED, route to the 'insecure'\n# index, and rename back to the original sourcetype.\n[mask_and_clone-clone]\n# SED is preferred over INGEST_EVAL replace() \u2014 compiled regex engine, and\n# you can chain commands with whitespace as the separator.\nSEDCMD-mask = s/email_address=(\\S\\S)\\S*(.)@(.)\\S*(\\S\\S\\S)\\s/email_address=\\1..\\2@\\3..\\4 /g s/password=\\S+/password=#######/g\n# Route the masked clone into a different index to prove the split.\nTRANSFORMS-route-to-index = shared-drop_useless_time_fields, shared-route_to_ingest_eval_examples_2\n# Reset the sourcetype back to the original so search-time consumers don't\n# have to know about the intermediate one.\nrename = mask_and_clone\n```\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n# Clone the event onto the mask_and_clone-clone sourcetype. The REGEX (.) on\n# the host field is the cheapest way to trigger a clone \u2014 we just need\n# something to match.\n[mask_and_clone-clone]\nSOURCE_KEY = MetaData:Host\nDEST_KEY = MetaData:Host\nREGEX = (.)\nFORMAT = %0\nCLONE_SOURCETYPE = mask_and_clone-clone\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {
		"ds_original": {
			"name": "Original events",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=\"ingest_eval_examples_1\" sourcetype=mask_and_clone",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "0",
					"latest": ""
				}
			}
		},
		"ds_masked": {
			"name": "Masked clone events",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=\"ingest_eval_examples_2\" sourcetype=mask_and_clone",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "0",
					"latest": ""
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"layout": {
		"globalInputs": [],
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 250
				},
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 1100
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_original",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 550
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_masked",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 550,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 550
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_props",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 1100,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 1100,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				]
			}
		},
		"options": {
			"submitButton": false
		},
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"label": "New tab",
					"layoutId": "layout_1"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"applicationProperties": {
		"hideEdit": false,
		"hideExport": false
	}
}
